{"metadata":{"title":"GtkBackend","modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While Gtk isn’t the preferred UI framework on every Linux distro, it’s the closest thing SwiftCrossUI has to a native Linux backend for now. The Qt backend may be brought back to life at some point to cover the rest of Linux distros."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For targetting older pre Gtk 4 Linux distros, see the secondary ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This backend supports Linux, macOS, and Windows, but its support for macOS has a few known issues worse due to underlying Gtk issues (and its support for Windows isn’t well tested).","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"System-dependencies","text":"System dependencies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you can use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"text":" you must install the required system dependencies for your platform. Here are installation instructions tailored to each supported platform;","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Linux","text":"Linux"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Debian-based distros","sudo apt install libgtk-4-dev clang","","# Fedora-based distros","sudo dnf install gtk4-devel clang"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 1: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"installing the required dependencies on Debian-based and Fedora-based Linux distros"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you run into errors related to not finding ","type":"text"},{"code":"gtk\/gtk.h","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project, try restarting your computer. This has worked in some cases (although there may be a more elegant solution).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are on a non-Debian non-Fedora distro and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" requirements end up differing significantly from the requirements stated above, please open a GitHub issue or PR so that we can improve the documentation."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"macOS","text":"macOS"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["brew install pkg-config gtk4"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 2: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"installing the required dependencies using Homebrew"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have Homebrew, installation instructions can be found at ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/brew.sh","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It should also be possible to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"gtk4","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" installed via MacPorts, but I have not tested that.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you run into errors related to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"libffi"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FFI"},{"type":"text","text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":", which can occur when certain older versions of the Xcode Command Line Tools are installed, try running the following command to patch libffi:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["sed -i '' 's\/-I..includedir.\/\/g' $(brew --prefix)\/Library\/Homebrew\/os\/mac\/pkgconfig\/*\/libffi.pc"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 3: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"fixing the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"libffi"},{"type":"text","text":" issue that some people face"}]}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Windows","text":"Windows"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows things are a bit complicated (as usual), so we only support installation via "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg"},{"type":"text","text":". First, install vcpkg;"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["git clone https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg C:\\vcpkg","C:\\vcpkg\\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 4: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install vcpkg (requires git cli)"}]}]},{"style":"warning","name":"Warning","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It’s important to install vcpkg at the root of a drive due to limitations of the Gtk build system.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After installation, make the following changes to your environment variables:"}]}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PKG_CONFIG_PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable to ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\lib\\pkgconfig","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This is only required for building.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to your ","type":"text"},{"code":"Path","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable. This is only required for running.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With vcpkg installed, you have two options for Gtk installation; global installation, and project-local installation","type":"text"}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","anchor":"Global-Gtk-4-installation-recommended","text":"Global Gtk 4 installation (recommended)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the command depends on your machine’s architecture; choose between Figure 5 and Figure 6 accordingly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Installation can take 45+ minutes depending on your machine.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet x64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 5: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install Gtk 4 globally on x64 Windows"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet arm64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 6: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install Gtk 4 globally on arm64 Windows"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"style":"warning","name":"Warning","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Run the chosen command at the root of your drive to ensure that vcpkg doesn’t run in manifest mode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","anchor":"Project-local-Gtk-4-installation-more-unreliable","text":"Project-local Gtk 4 installation (more unreliable)"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the absolute path to your project contains spaces, it is possible that vcpkg will break, and installing globally will be a more reliable strategy."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To install Gtk 4 in a project-local dependency store you must setup a ","type":"text"},{"code":"vcpkg.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" manifest file and then run vcpkg, as detailed below;","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First ","type":"text"},{"code":"vcpkg.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" at the root of your project and make sure that it includes the ","type":"text"},{"code":"gtk","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" dependency as demonstrated in Figure 7.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["{","    \"name\": \"project-name\",","    \"version-string\": \"main\",","    \"dependencies\": [\"gtk\"]","}"],"syntax":"json"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 7: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"an example ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vcpkg.json"},{"text":" package manifest","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install --triplet x64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 8: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"install the dependencies listed in your package manifest","type":"text"}]}]},{"style":"warning","name":"Warning","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace the triplet with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arm64-windows"},{"type":"text","text":" if you’re on ARM64"}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Usage","text":"Usage"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["...","","let package = Package(","  ...","  targets: [","    ...","    .executableTarget(","      name: \"YourApp\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"SwiftCrossUI\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","        .product(name: \"GtkBackend\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","      ]","    )","    ...","  ]","  ...",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 9: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"adding ","type":"text"},{"code":"GtkBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to an executable target","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import SwiftCrossUI","import GtkBackend","","@main","s